## B.3 Baselines for Comparison

For KGQA, we consider the following three types of baseline methods for performance comparison:

- subgraph-based reasoning methods which perform answer reasoning in a retrieval subgraph form KG, including GrafeNet [\(Sun et al.,](#page-10-8) [2018\)](#page-10-8), NSM [\(He et al.,](#page-9-8) [2021\)](#page-9-8), SubgraphRetrieval [\(Zhang](#page-11-8) [et al.,](#page-11-8) [2022\)](#page-11-8), UniKGQA [\(Jiang et al.,](#page-9-13) [2023d\)](#page-9-13), and ReasoningLM [\(Jiang et al.,](#page-9-14) [2023c\)](#page-9-14) for datasets on Freebase, and KVMemNet [\(Miller et al.,](#page-9-15) [2016\)](#page-9-15), EmbedKGQA [\(Saxena et al.,](#page-10-9) [2020\)](#page-10-9), and RGCN [\(Schlichtkrull et al.,](#page-10-10) [2018\)](#page-10-10) for datasets on Wikidata;
